            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer against thieves and sorcerers, the latter being referred to as 'qamaññā', which Stefan Strelcyn identified as a 
                    "sorcerer who makes people ill using philtres and poisons" (cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1972Wellcome"/>
                     <citedRange unit="page">51</citedRange></bibl>).
                    Thematically similar to <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6781PPAynat"/>.</p>
